RIYADH: Members of the Saudi Arabian Scouts Association guided over 92,000 lost pilgrims between Dhu Al-Hijjah 7-13, Saudi Press Agency reported on Tuesday. A total of 92,592 pilgrims of various nationalities were guided by the scouts to their destinations. Of these pilgrims, 6,976 were taken to their camps and 85,616 were given advice and shown the way to their destination. More than 110 scouts guided the pilgrims from six sites in Mina during the Hajj period.